HEADWORD: Quaintise
<hw>Quain"tise</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>cointise</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Craft; subtlety;
cunning.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer. R. of
Glouces.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Elegance; beauty.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quaintly</ent>⟦br⟧
